#: ../../G/gumby.rst:5
msgid "gumby"
msgstr "gumby"

#: ../../G/gumby.rst:7
msgid "/guhm´bee/, n\\."
msgstr "/guhm´bee/, 名詞"

#: ../../G/gumby.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from a class of Monty Python characters, poss. with some influence from the"
" 1960s claymation character]"
msgstr "[Monty Pythonのあるクラスのキャラクターより。おそらく1960年代のクレイアニメのキャラクターからの影響もある]"

#: ../../G/gumby.rst:13
msgid ""
"An act of minor but conspicuous stupidity, often in gumby maneuver or pull a"
" gumby."
msgstr "ささいだが目立つ愚行。しばしばgumby maneuver(gumby作戦)やpull a gumby(gumbyをやらかす)の形で。"

#: ../../G/gumby.rst:16
msgid ""
"[NRL] n. A bureaucrat, or other technical incompetent who impedes the "
"progress of real work."
msgstr "[NRL] 名詞 官僚、あるいは本物の仕事の進行を妨げる、その他の技術的に無能な人。"

#: ../../G/gumby.rst:18
msgid ""
"adj. Relating to things typically associated with people in sense 2. (e.g. "
"\"Ran would be writing code, but Richard gave him gumby work that's due on "
"Friday\", or, \"Dammit! Travel screwed up my plane tickets. I have to go out"
" on gumby patrol.\")"
msgstr ""
"形容詞 "
"語義2の人々と典型的に結びつくものに関連する。(たとえば「Ranはコードを書いているはずなんだが、Richardが金曜締め切りのgumbyな仕事を彼に与えた」とか、「くそっ!出張部門が私の航空券をめちゃくちゃにした。gumbyパトロールに出なきゃならん」)"
